##Mink, Fox, raccoon dog removed from edible list behind: zoonosis

Introduction: Experts suggest that the catalogue of livestock and poultry genetic resources should be revised as soon as possible to remove the terrestrial wild animals raised by artificial breeding such as mink, raccoon dog, deer family, ostrich family and pheasant family

Author | first finance, Zangke

The fur of mink, Fox and raccoon dog is on me. Where's the meat? Is the meat of these wild animals edible? Today (the 26th) , the question was raised again.

At the 16th meeting of the 13th Standing Committee of the National People's Congress on February 24th, the decision was adopted by the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress on comprehensively prohibiting illegal wildlife trade, eradicating abusive practices of eating wild animals, and earnestly safeguarding the health and safety of the People (hereinafter referred to as the decision) .

The decision clearly stipulates that the State Council and its relevant departments, as well as provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities directly under the Central Government shall, in accordance with this decision and relevant laws, formulate and adjust relevant lists and supporting provisions.

After the first finance and economics published the Article "after the total "Ban Wild" , which wild animals can still eat? " Yesterday, it soon received a number of responses.

"In 2003, the former Ministry of Forestry published a list of 54 species of terrestrial wildlife that were commercially exploited to mature through domestication and breeding techniques, " Su Peifen, founder of the China Green Development Council Action Asia Fund, told China Business News, the breeding of mink, Fox and raccoon dog was included in the successful breeding species. The former Ministry of Agriculture "China Livestock Genetic Resources Directory" (2017) will also be Silver Fox, Blue Fox, mink, raccoon dog and other included in the list of livestock. This means that wild animals such as minks, foxes, and raccoon dogs can be put on the menu.

But "from Severe Acute Respiratory System Syndrome (SARS) to COVID-19 pneumonia COVID-19, a common denominator is that both diseases are associated with inappropriate or close contact with wild animals, " she said, in the light of Articles 2 and 3 of the decision, attention needs to be paid to those wild land animals included in the inventory of livestock resources, and the treatment of these wild animals will be the key to the full implementation of the decision.

Taking mink, Fox and raccoon dog as examples, Su Peifen said that relevant departments have all along regarded mink, Fox and raccoon dog as resources to promote the captive breeding of fur animals and encourage fur animal breeding to be included as part of promoting rural economic development. Fur Industry is regarded as a low-cost, high-profit industry.

Source: CARCASS TREATMENT EQUIPMENT FOR MINK and raccoon dog in a wild animal breeding base in Hebei Province. Photo by Zangke

Public data show that the largest mink farming province in Shandong Province, accounting for about 71.28% of the total amount of mink fur. Liaoning Province ranked second, accounting for 17.54 percent. Heilongjiang was third with 6.19 per cent.

Shandong Province is also the largest Fox breeding province, accounting for about 40.55% of the total fox skin. Hebei Province ranked second with 29.09 percent. Liaoning Province ranked third, accounting for 18.33 percent. Foxes in the three provinces accounted for about 87.97 percent of the total number of skins taken by foxes in China.

The biggest province of breeding racoon dog is Hebei Province, which accounts for 66.32% of the total skin of racoon dog in China. Shandong Province ranked second, accounting for 24.85 percent. Heilongjiang was third with about 5.28 per cent. The amount of skin taken from raccoon dog in three provinces is about 96.45% of the total skin taken from raccoon dog in China.

The investigation by the China Green Hair Association and other organizations found that there were cases in which the mink, Fox and raccoon dog meat were sold on the food market as other meat products. On the Menu Board of a game restaurant in Wuhan's south China market, which is suspected to have its origins in COVID-19, it is openly listed as selling Fox meat, mink meat, or live minks.

China's fur animals have ten million carcasses a year, according to the report on Sustainable Development Strategy of China's wildlife breeding industry by the Chinese Academy of Engineering, a consultancy and research project, in 2015, the peak year for fur production, there were about 95 million carcasses of fur animals of mink, Fox and raccoon dog, totaling about 1.24 million tons, all of which were taken away by itinerant traders, some of which were used as meat and bone meal feed, there are a large number of other meat into the market on the table, because of no quarantine, on the table easily lead to food safety issues.

According to a report in 2013 by Qingdao Internet radio and television station "Love Qingdao, " titled "Rotten mink meat is used as ham sausage, police investigation has been traced" , mINK, once in a while, is pulled out at night, "and sold to an illegal processing plant in Wulian County.

A report titled "wal-mart's purchase is revealed to be related to profit transfer: 10 times the difference between the price of real donkey meat, " was published on the China Economic Network on January 10,2014, "At first, the producers did not dare to replace donkey meat with Fox meat in the course of their cooperation with Walmart, but in the course of the cooperation, the producers found that Walmart did not exercise particularly strict supervision and that many links in the later stages were virtually nonexistent. The producers mixed some Starch Fox meat with donkey meat in order to reduce costs. " A kilo of raw donkey meat on the market costs 25 yuan, the price of cooked donkey meat is 40 yuan. Some industry insiders said that if the Fox meat instead of donkey, into the price differential at least 10 times.

Source: a Wildlife Farm in Shandong Province. Photo by Zangke

In July 2019, a Guangming Website report titled "Hot Noodles is just the tip of the iceberg. " These snacks hurt the spleen and stomach, telling children: don't eat them. " "The cheapest bag of sausages is only 18 yuan, but there are 52 of them inside, and the average one is only 30 cents, " he said. "according to industry insiders, a regular sausage factory uses chicken breasts, chicken skin and duck skin to make sausages, and then uses pork flavor, monascus pigment, preservatives and starch to spice up, color and stuff them. There are also factories that use Fox meat and mink meat, which are very cheap. ".

For mink, Fox and Raccoon Dog, which are listed in the Chinese livestock and Poultry Genetic Resources Directory, Zhang Yuanyuan, director of Action Asia Life Care Education and a graduate of the Sun Yat-sen University of Medical Sciences, told China Business News, in the context of food safety and health, the issue of where the skin is removed should not only be a concern, but also the issue of zoonosis.

A retrospective clinical study of hospitalized patients infected with a novel Bunia virus, published in the Chinese Journal of Infectious Diseases, found that 22 of the 68 patients had a history of marten breeding or being bitten by a mink, Zhang Yuanyuan said. The 68 cases were all laboratory confirmed by the Wendeng Central Hospital in Weihai, while the Wendeng mink is a local product of Wendeng District in Weihai, Shandong Province, and is regarded as the geographical symbol of agricultural products in the country.

The study also found that minks can be infected with H5N1 as well as human flu, providing an opportunity for further complex evolution of the virus, said Avian Influenza, a researcher at the University of California, San Diego. In addition, the MINK has prion disease, coronavirus enteritis, Brucellosis, eperythrozoonosis and so on.

"Therefore, we can see that the listing of foxes, minks and raccoon dogs on the livestock genetic resources inventory is extremely dangerous, both in terms of the health problems associated with meat consumption and the risk of disease in the farming industry, " she said, it is suggested that relevant departments should re-examine the catalogue of livestock and poultry genetic resources as soon as possible and remove the terrestrial wild animals in the catalogue, such as mink, raccoon dog, deer family, ostrich family, pheasant family, etc. , in order to effectively protect the people's health and safety.

To avoid a repeat of the public health and health crises caused by trading and eating "game meat, " the China Law Society recently recommended that, the establishment and improvement of wildlife management measures listed in the manual breeding List of endangered and protected species of China, including a permit system for manual breeding, and production-specific labeling, and a system of traceability for the sale and use of the animals and their products of the stock accordingly.
